 The Lagos State Commissioner for Information and Strategy, Kehinde Bamigbetan, Sunday, was involved in a near-death auto-crash after the car in which he was travelling collided with an armoured car. PHOTO: Facebook/Kehinde Bamigbetan  Bamigbetan and his driver were returning from his farm when the accident occurred. “The driver drove into an armoured carrier on our way from the farm. I was taking a nap in the rear seat,” the commissioner said in a Facebook post. Bamigbetan sustained visible cuts to his forehead and the car’s front part was extensively damaged. He said his driver ran into the armoured personnel carrier with plate number NPF 8610 C after he dozed while driving. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .